.TH LINKEDIN\-MCP\-SERVER 1 "2026-05-11" "4.13.0" "LinkedIn MCP Server"
.SH NAME
linkedin\-mcp\-server \- MCP server for LinkedIn profile, company, and job scraping
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B linkedin\-mcp\-server
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B linkedin\-mcp\-server
is a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server that enables AI assistants such as
Claude to interact with LinkedIn via an automated Chromium browser session.
It exposes tools for scraping person profiles, company pages, job listings,
and the LinkedIn feed.
.PP
The server supports two transport modes.
In \fBstdio\fR mode (the default) it communicates with an MCP client over
standard input/output and is suitable for direct process-level integration.
In \fBstreamable-http\fR mode it listens on a local HTTP endpoint.
.PP
Before running the server for the first time, authenticate with LinkedIn
using \fB\-\-login\fR.
The resulting browser profile is stored under
.I ~/.linkedin\-mcp/profile/
and reused on subsequent starts.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Session management
.TP
.B \-\-login
Open an interactive browser window for LinkedIn authentication and save the
resulting profile.
Exits after the profile is saved.
.TP
.B \-\-status
Check whether the saved session is still valid and exit.
Exits with code\~0 on success, 1 on failure.
.TP
.B \-\-logout
Clear the stored LinkedIn browser profile and exit.
.SS Transport
.TP
\fB\-\-transport\fR \fIstdio\fR|\fIstreamable\-http\fR
Select the MCP transport.
\fBstdio\fR (default) communicates over standard input/output.
\fBstreamable\-http\fR starts an HTTP server.
.TP
\fB\-\-host\fR \fIHOST\fR
Hostname or IP address for the HTTP server (default: \fB127.0.0.1\fR).
Binding to \fB0.0.0.0\fR exposes the endpoint to all network interfaces;
the MCP endpoint has no built-in authentication.
.TP
\fB\-\-port\fR \fIPORT\fR
TCP port for the HTTP server (default: \fB8000\fR).
.TP
\fB\-\-path\fR \fIPATH\fR
URL path for the HTTP endpoint (default: \fB/mcp\fR).
.SS Browser
.TP
.B \-\-no\-headless
Run Chromium with a visible window.
Useful during login and for debugging scraping issues.
.TP
\fB\-\-user\-data\-dir\fR \fIPATH\fR
Directory used to persist the Chromium profile
(default: \fB~/.linkedin\-mcp/profile\fR).
.TP
\fB\-\-chrome\-path\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to a custom Chrome or Chromium executable.
Uses the patchright-managed browser by default.
.TP
\fB\-\-viewport\fR \fIWxH\fR
Browser viewport dimensions (default: \fB1280x720\fR).
.TP
\fB\-\-timeout\fR \fIMS\fR
Timeout for individual browser page operations in milliseconds
(default: \fB5000\fR).
.TP
\fB\-\-slow\-mo\fR \fIMS\fR
Delay every browser action by \fIMS\fR milliseconds.
Useful for debugging.
.TP
\fB\-\-user\-agent\fR \fISTRING\fR
Override the browser User-Agent header.
.SS Server
.TP
\fB\-\-tool\-timeout\fR \fISECONDS\fR
Per-tool MCP execution timeout in seconds (default: \fB180.0\fR).
.TP
\fB\-\-log\-level\fR \fIDEBUG\fR|\fIINFO\fR|\fIWARNING\fR|\fIERROR\fR
Set the logging verbosity (default: \fBWARNING\fR).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
Environment variables are read before command-line arguments and can be
overridden by them.
.TP
.B HEADLESS
Set to \fB0\fR, \fBfalse\fR, \fBno\fR, or \fBoff\fR to disable headless mode.
Set to \fB1\fR, \fBtrue\fR, \fByes\fR, or \fBon\fR to enable it.
.TP
.B LOG_LEVEL
Logging level: \fBDEBUG\fR, \fBINFO\fR, \fBWARNING\fR, or \fBERROR\fR.
.TP
.B TRANSPORT
Transport mode: \fBstdio\fR or \fBstreamable\-http\fR.
.TP
.B HOST
HTTP server host.
.TP
.B PORT
HTTP server port.
.TP
.B HTTP_PATH
HTTP server URL path.
.TP
.B TIMEOUT
Browser page-operation timeout in milliseconds.
.TP
.B TOOL_TIMEOUT
Per-tool MCP execution timeout in seconds.
.TP
.B USER_AGENT
Custom browser User-Agent string.
.TP
.B VIEWPORT
Browser viewport in \fIWxH\fR format, e.g.\& \fB1920x1080\fR.
.TP
.B SLOW_MO
Browser action delay in milliseconds.
.TP
.B CHROME_PATH
Path to a custom Chrome/Chromium executable.
.TP
.B USER_DATA_DIR
Path to the persistent Chromium profile directory.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.linkedin\-mcp/profile/
Default directory for the persistent Chromium browser profile and
authentication state.
A \fB.env\fR file in the current working directory is loaded automatically
if present.
.SH EXAMPLES
Authenticate with LinkedIn for the first time:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
linkedin\-mcp\-server \-\-login
.EE
.RE
.PP
Start the server in stdio mode (default, for MCP client integration):
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
linkedin\-mcp\-server \-\-transport stdio
.EE
.RE
.PP
Start the server in HTTP mode:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
linkedin\-mcp\-server \-\-transport streamable\-http \-\-port 8080
.EE
.RE
.PP
Check whether the current session is still valid:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
linkedin\-mcp\-server \-\-status
.EE
.RE
